  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various approaches, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Use of advanced digital forensic tools\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n\n4. Prosecution Strategies\n- Criminal charges for money laundering\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Technological Monitoring\n- Advanced transaction tracking systems\n- Artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms\n- Real-time suspicious activity detection\n\nThese methods aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and technological approaches.",
